Program: Discovery
Title: The Moon
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jryt8
Last Broadcast Date: 02 November 2004
The origins of the moon - and how essential it has been to the evolution of life. The moon landings improved our understanding of our nearest neighbour; it is a belief that the moon was formed from a collision with the early earth. A small amount split off and over millions of years formed into our moon. Show less